; Mazra'eh (farm) — 01_CORE_MECHANICS.md §5
; status: calibrated — cost anchored to spec (60 coin per §5). construction_ticks=540
;   derived via Phase-3-session-3 open consultation (timing ladder rationale documented).
;   max_hp=300 calibrated by parity with Ma'dan (soft economy target framing).
; Generates grain (via worker-gathered ResourceNode, per RESOURCE_NODE_CONTRACT.md).
; "60 coin" per spec. Medium HP — farms should be raidable but not trivially destroyed.
; farr_per_tick = 0 — farms don't generate Farr.
;
; construction_ticks = 540 = 18s @ 30Hz. Grain is the gating resource for all
; Farr-generating buildings (Atashkadeh: 50 grain, Dadgah: 75 grain) and unit
; upkeep. Slightly shorter build than Ma'dan (22s) to reward players who
; prioritize grain infrastructure first — grain unlocks are upstream of coin
; multipliers in the tech path. Timing ladder: Khaneh (3s placeholder) <
; Mazra'eh (18s) < Ma'dan (22s) < Atashkadeh (30s) < Qal'eh (90s per §8).
; Cultural note: dehqan stewardship — patient agriculture is a civilizational
; value, not a quick transaction; 18s reflects meaningful labor without being
; punishing.
; balance-engineer: Phase 3 session 3 wave 1C open consultation.
[sub_resource type="Resource" id="bldg_mazraeh"]
script = ExtResource("3_bldgstats")
max_hp = 300.0
coin_cost = 60
grain_cost = 0
construction_ticks = 540
farr_per_tick = 0.0

; Ma'dan (مَعدَن, mine / source) — 01_CORE_MECHANICS.md §5
; status: calibrated — coin_cost=40 anchored to spec (§5 explicit). modifier_value_x100=150
;   calibrated (50% yield boost — 2.0× rejected as degenerate, rationale documented).
;   construction_ticks=660 from timing-ladder open consultation. No live-test of
;   mine-exploitation economy under real combat pressure yet.
; Buff-emitter building. When placed within modifier_radius_m of a MineNode,
; registers itself with that mine and multiplies effective coin_yield_per_trip
; by modifier_value_x100 / 100 (fixed-point per Sim Contract §1.6).
;
; Cost: "40 coin" per spec (01_CORE_MECHANICS.md §5 table — explicit, not a
; suggestion). grain_cost = 0: Tier-1 infrastructure, no grain gate.
;
; modifier_value_x100 = 150 → 1.5× yield multiplier. 50% boost is meaningful
; without becoming degenerate. 2.0× (200) would trivialize economy — two Ma'dans
; on one mine would double income before mid-game pressure arrives.
;
; modifier_radius_m = 4.0 → matches FOG_DATA_CONTRACT cell size ("one cell of
; adjacency" framing from kickoff §3 wave 1B). Stored as float; this is a
; spatial config, not a fixed-point gameplay value.
;
; modifier_stacks = false → first-registered-wins; multiple Ma'dans on the same
; mine do NOT compound. Stacking would create a "pile Ma'dans on one mine"
; degenerate strategy. Kickoff default confirmed — no reason to flip.
;
; HP 300.0 = Mazra'eh parity: mine enhancers and farms are both soft economy
; targets, should fall to the same sustained raiding pressure.
;
; construction_ticks = 660 = 22s @ 30Hz. Ma'dan is a multiplicative economic
; power spike (+50% coin yield via modifier_value_x100 = 150 on the bonded
; MineNode). Its impact is immediate and strong — a slightly longer build time
; than Mazra'eh (540 = 18s) creates a meaningful build-order decision: rush
; Ma'dan for coin power, or build Mazra'eh first to unlock grain-gated
; buildings (Atashkadeh, Dadgah). 4-second gap is perceptible; 22s is not
; punishing. Timing ladder: Khaneh (3s placeholder) < Mazra'eh (18s) <
; Ma'dan (22s) < Atashkadeh (30s) < Qal'eh (90s per §8).
; Cultural note: Pishdadian civilizational labor (Hushang → Tahmuras →
; Jamshid arc) — discovering mineral wealth is deliberate, not instant.
; balance-engineer: Phase 3 session 3 wave 1C open consultation.
;
; NEW FIELDS (modifier_value_x100, modifier_radius_m, modifier_stacks):
; BuildingStats script does not yet declare these @export fields — gp-sys adds
; them in wave 1B. Godot .tres tolerates extra fields gracefully; pre-shipped
; here so gp-sys reads final values directly (per lead recommendation, kickoff).
;
; DECISIONS.md ref: wave 1B Option B — Ma'dan is a buff-emitter, NOT a Coin
; producer. Ma'dan does NOT produce Coin itself; it boosts adjacent MineNodes.
[sub_resource type="Resource" id="bldg_madan"]
script = ExtResource("3_bldgstats")
max_hp = 300.0
coin_cost = 40
grain_cost = 0
construction_ticks = 660
farr_per_tick = 0.0
modifier_value_x100 = 150
modifier_radius_m = 4.0
modifier_stacks = false

; Sarbaz-khaneh (barracks) — 01_CORE_MECHANICS.md §5
; status: calibrated — coin_cost=100 anchored to spec (§5). construction_ticks=780
;   from timing-ladder open consultation (symmetric 120-tick gaps above Ma'dan and
;   below Atashkadeh). max_hp=400, training costs all calibrated at Wave 3A.6.
; Produces Tier 1 military: Piyade, Kamandar. "100 coin" per spec.
; Medium-high HP — not as durable as Atashkadeh (sacred flame) but must
; survive a raid long enough for garrisoned units to react.
; farr_per_tick = 0 — barracks do not generate Farr.
;
; construction_ticks = 780 = 26s @ 30Hz.
; Timing-ladder anchoring (agent-def discipline, session-3 retro §C):
;   Khaneh(90=3s) < Mazra'eh(540=18s) < Ma'dan(660=22s)
;   < Sarbaz-khaneh(780=26s) < Atashkadeh(900=30s) < Qal'eh(2700=90s per §8)
;
; Why 780, not the briefed 720-900 band endpoints:
;   - Above Ma'dan (660): military commitment is strategically heavier than a
;     coin multiplier. You cannot produce combat units without this building;
;     the build time must register as a deliberate choice, not a quick dispatch.
;   - Below Atashkadeh (900): the Farr/Tier-2 gateway remains the costliest
;     Tier-1 build. Sarbaz-khaneh is urgent but not a tier gate — 4s separation
;     below Atashkadeh preserves that distinction.
;   - 780 sits exactly 120 ticks (4s) above Ma'dan and 120 ticks (4s) below
;     Atashkadeh — symmetric gaps, both perceptible at 15-25 min match pacing
;     (01_CORE_MECHANICS.md §2.2).
;
; Cost-ladder monotonicity: NOT strictly monotonic by cost (Ma'dan 40 coin
; costs less than Khaneh 50 but takes longer to build — justified by
; multiplicative yield impact). Sarbaz-khaneh (100 coin) sits correctly above
; Ma'dan in ticks because its strategic necessity warrants the commitment,
; not because cost alone dictates it.
;
; Cultural note: Sarbaz-khaneh formalizes WHO is a soldier (oath, training,
; role-definition). The 26s build frames it as an institutional commitment —
; not the snap decision of equipping a militiaman, but the founding of an
; organized military corps. §5 spec: "Sarbaz-khaneh (barracks) — Produces
; Tier 1 military: Piyade, Kamandar. 100 coin."
; balance-engineer: Phase 3 session 4 wave 2A open consultation.
[sub_resource type="Resource" id="bldg_sarbaz_khaneh"]
script = ExtResource("3_bldgstats")
max_hp = 400.0
coin_cost = 100
grain_cost = 0
construction_ticks = 780
farr_per_tick = 0.0
; Wave 3A.6 training schema (H3 first-exercise, balance-engineer Track 3):
; Costs align with UnitStats.coin_cost / grain_cost (Piyade: 50c/10g) — the
; per-unit cost intent set at unit-design time. BuildingStats fields enable
; future per-producer overrides without touching UnitStats.
; Dwell 90 ticks = 3s @ 30Hz per brief §1 starting point (faster than
; UnitStats.production_ticks=600 to keep MVP loop snappy).
; §9.L1: spec is silent on training costs; brief values are starting points.
; Using UnitStats values as canonical source for coin/grain; brief dwell kept.
train_piyade_cost_coin = 50
train_piyade_cost_grain = 10
train_piyade_dwell_ticks = 90

; Atashkadeh (fire temple) — 01_CORE_MECHANICS.md §5
; status: calibrated — coin_cost=150/grain_cost=50 anchored to spec (§5 SSOT). max_hp=600
;   spec-wins override (brief suggested 400; §4.3 −5 Farr drain named it qualitatively
;   distinct). construction_ticks=900 from timing-ladder. farr_per_tick + farr_per_min_x100
;   anchored to §4.3 (+1 Farr/min). Farr drain rates anchored to Phase-3 open space resolution.
; Cost: "150 coin, 50 grain" per §5 Tier-1 table (spec-SSOT; not a suggestion).
; Prerequisite for Tier 2 advance (Qal'eh requires Atashkadeh built, per §8).
;
; Farr: +1 Farr/min continuous passive emit per §4.3 Farr generators list.
;   farr_per_tick = 0.000556 = 1/1800 Farr/tick @ 30Hz (float path, FarrSystem today).
;   farr_per_min_x100 = 100 = +1 Farr/min in x100 fixed-point per Sim Contract §1.6
;   (integer path — first instance; forward-compat for Dadgah=50, Barghah=50,
;   Yadgar=25 per §4.3 generators list). Both fields encode the same source value.
;
; Loss drain: −5 Farr per §4.3 Drains ("the sacred flame is extinguished").
; This cost motivates max_hp = 600 — the sacred flame warrants more durability
; than the barracks (400) or resource buildings (300). hp=400 (brief suggestion)
; would be a regression; spec-wins: §4.3's −5 Farr drain names the sacred flame
; as a qualitatively distinct loss event.
;
; construction_ticks = 900 = 30s @ 30Hz. Timing-ladder anchor:
;   Khaneh(90=3s) < Mazra'eh(540=18s) < Ma'dan(660=22s)
;   < Sarbaz-khaneh(780=26s) < Atashkadeh(900=30s) < Qal'eh(2700=90s per §8)
; Atashkadeh is the slowest Tier-1 build — appropriate for the Tier-2 gateway.
; balance-engineer: Wave 2A.5 D9 audit + farr_per_min_x100 schema addition.
[sub_resource type="Resource" id="bldg_atashkadeh"]
script = ExtResource("3_bldgstats")
max_hp = 600.0
coin_cost = 150
grain_cost = 50
construction_ticks = 900
farr_per_tick = 0.000556
farr_per_min_x100 = 100

; Sowari-khaneh (سواری‌خانه, cavalry stable) — 01_CORE_MECHANICS.md §5
; status: calibrated — coin_cost=200 anchored to spec (§5 Tier-2 table). max_hp=750 and
;   construction_ticks=1080 from Wave 2B open consultation (HP/tick ladder rationale
;   documented). Training costs from Wave 3A.6 (UnitStats canonical source). Tier-2
;   consumers deferred to Phase 4.
; Produces Savar (cavalry). "200 coin" per §5 Tier-2 table (line 194).
; grain_cost = 0: Tier-2 institutional buildings are coin-economy-framed;
; only the Tier-2 upgrade itself (Qal'eh) and sacral buildings carry grain.
;
; construction_ticks = 1080 = 36s @ 30Hz. Timing-ladder anchoring:
;   Khaneh(90=3s) < Mazra'eh(540=18s) < Ma'dan(660=22s)
;   < Sarbaz-khaneh(780=26s) < Atashkadeh(900=30s)
;   < Tirandazi(960=32s) < Sowari-khaneh(1080=36s) < Qal'eh(2700=90s per §8)
; Sowari-khaneh > Tirandazi: cavalry stables require more complex construction
; (stalls, equipment, training yard) than an archery training ground.
; Both Tier-2 buildings placed above Atashkadeh — Tier-2 commitment must feel
; heavier than the Tier-1 gateway, not equal to it.
;
; max_hp = 750: Tier-2 institutional with heavy equipment (warhorses). Above
; Sarbaz-khaneh (400) and Atashkadeh (600); below Throne (2000). HP ladder
; respects Tier-2 > Tier-1 without approaching the capital's durability.
;
; tier = 2: FIRST non-default value of BuildingStats.tier (H3 dormant-schema
; first-exercise, Wave 2B Track 3). Consumers DEFERRED to Wave 2C / Phase 4
; per §9.H3 documented chain: TechSystem / BuildPlacementHandler / BuildMenu /
; Atashkadeh-built + Farr >= 40 prereq logic.
;
; Spec refs: 01_CORE_MECHANICS.md §5 (200 coin, Tier-2 table).
; balance-engineer: Wave 2B Track 3 — H3 + L6 inaugural dogfood.
[sub_resource type="Resource" id="bldg_sowari_khaneh"]
